oks and novels on morals / Nabawiya Musa -- The difference between men and women / Nabawiya Musa -- Unveiling and veiling / Nazira Zain al-Din -- The young woman and the Shaikhs / Nazira Zain al-Din -- Double standard / Saiza Nabarawi -- The voice of happiness / Zoubeida Bittari -- The gate of heaven is open / Farida Benlyazid -- Two faces, one woman / Nuha Samara -- From Tumbling on the Snow / Huda Naamani -- Who\'s cleverer: Man or woman? / Fatima Mernissi -- My life / Chaibia -- Eight eyes / Sufi Abdallah -- Pan-Arabism / Huda Shaarawi -- Arab women\'s intellectual heritage / Zahiya Dughan -- We Egyptian women / Inji Aflatun -- Islam and the Constitutional Rights of Women / Duriya Shafiq -- Feast of unveiling / Amina Said -- Why, Reverend Shaikh? / Amina Said -- Challenges facing the Arab woman at the end of 20th century / Nahid Toubia -- Legal rights of the Egyptian woman / A group of Egyptian women -- An unveiled voice / Amatalrauf al-Sharki -- Introduction to Nawal al-Saadawi\'s Ferdaous / Assia Djebar -- TRANSITIONS: Women\'s rights are human rights are Islamic rights / Amat al-Aleem Alsoswa -- Egyptian women finally get their due / Tahani al-Jibali -- Testimonial of a creative woman / Latifa Al-Zayyat -- Road / Huda Ablan -- Belongings / Huda Ablan -- Confession / Huda Ablan -- Spillage / Huda Ablan -- Setting sail / Huda Ablan -- How to become a man / Ibtisam al-Mutawakkal -- The first letters / Ibtisam al-Mutawakkal -- Documenting / Nabila Zubair -- Still / Nabila Zubair -- From national resistance to feminist activism / Kuwaiti Activists -- Another role for Abaya / Layla al-Uthman -- Sacred narratives linking Iraqi Shiite women / Tayba Hassan Al Khalifa Sharif -- Bab al-Saha / Sahar Khalifa -- Glossary -- Index\n\n   ', '', '', '', 'Women\'s Studies, Middle East Studies', 'xlvii, 461 p. ; 25 cm.', '2nd ed.', '0253344417', '06/06/2006', 'translit', 'book');
