INSERT INTO `main_table` VALUES ('1263', 'Verse', '', '', '', '', 'C. George Fry and James R. King', '', '', '', 'An anthology of Middle Eastern Literature from the Twentieth Century', '', '', '', '', '', 'Ohio, U.S.A.', '1974', 'Introduction -- I. THE LAST ISLAMIC EMPIRE, 1898-1914: from the Daughter of Egypt / Yaqub Saruf -- Freom the Lily of the Valley / Amin al-Rihani -- From Bread / Tawfiq Awwad -- Revolution / Jamil Sidqi Al-Zahawi -- Ramadan is over / Ahmed Shawqi -- How to forget / Bishara Al-Khuri -- The abandoned chateau / Ahmed Rami -- Jesus / Rashid Salim Al-Khuri -- The feminine spirit / Abd al-Rahman al-Siddiq -- The return of spring / Abd al-Rahman al-Siddiq -- Fatalism and predestination / Mohammad Abdouh and Gamal al-Din al-Afghani -- The liberation of the Oriental woman / Qasim Amin -- Despotism and Science in Occident and Orient / Abd al-Rahman al-Kawakibi -- II. THE MIDDLE EAST AND TWO WORLD WARS, 1914-1945:  From Once upon a Time / Mikail Naima -- A night in the valley from In the Days of the Emir / Fouad Efrem Boustani -- The Gaucho from the Execution / Khalil Taki al-Deen -- Honor / Maroun Abboud -- Military Service from Zeinab / Muhammad Husain Haikal -- A woman of Thirty. from A Painful Lesson / Chehata Ebeid -- Eve without Adam / Mahmoud Taher Lachin -- Osta Chehata, The Coachman, from Cairo / Mamoud Taimur -- The beauties of Sayeda Zeinab / Saleh Dhohni -- Om Tammam, from The Damned of the Earth / Taha Hussein -- Summer Visitors in Chains / Tawfiq al Hakim -- The Donkey Market / Tawfiq al Hakim -- If / Mikail Nuami -- The moon / Said Akl -- Nayanar / Said Akl -- My brother / Ahmed al Mukhtar al-Wazir -- If / Nazir Kabbani -- To a visitor / Bichr Fares -- Six candles / Edwige Chayboub -- Granada / Faouzi Maalouf -- Cataract / Amine Nakhle -- Sodom / Elias Chabaki -- To a woman / Joseph Noujaim -- Prayer / Salah Labaki -- Correspondences / Chokrallah al-Jorr -- Ruined Castle / Omar Richa -- The moon at Manchester / Abdullah al-Tayyeb -- We are Arabs / Abdullah Abdel Rahman -- Science and us / Muhammad Mahdi al-Bassir -- A story / Muhammad Mahdi al Jawahiri -- Ancients and Moderns, from On Pre-Islamic Poetry / Taha Hussein -- The Mediterranean sources of Egyptian Culture, from The Future of Egyptian Culture / Taha Hussein -- From The Stream of Days / Taha Hussein -- III. EGYPT AND NASSERISM: The Lamp of Om Hachem / Yehia Haqqi -- The Fashioner of Sick Men, from Midaq Alley / Naguib Mahfouz -- From The Water Carrier is Dead / Yousef el-Sebai -- A heap of flesh, from The Cries of The People / Abd Al Rahman el-Khamissi -- The Fight from The Earth / Abd el-Rahman el-Charqawi -- The Were Seven from The Least Dear Nights / Youssef Idris -- The Field of Corn / Moukhtar el-Attar -- PROSE AND POETRY OF MODERN EGYPT: Islam against Western Thought / Mohammad al-Bahey -- The continuity of the Egyptian Personality / Hussein Fawzi -- Toward an Egyptian culture / Mahmoud Amin al-Alem -- Farewell / Ahmed Abdel Muty Hijazi -- IV. THE MAGHRIB: A man\'s hand, from Algerian Shadows / Abd el-Hamid Ben Haddouqa -- From The Tenament / Mohammed Dib -- Tarnanno / Mohammed Rachad Hamazawi -- The Fruitpicker / Mohammed Faraj el-Chazli --  In the City / Abd el-Jabbar el-Sahimi -- Algeria / Muhammed al-id Khalifa -- Hurt holiday / Salih Kharifi -- I do not hesitate / Aboulkassem Kerrou -- Where? / Ahmed Khereddine -- Galatea / Jaafar Majed -- Revolution / Mustafa Maadaoui -- Carthage / Mustafa Maadaoui -- The Mosque and Instruction / Abd al-Ahmed Ben Badis -- From Journal / Mouloud Feraoun -- V. ISRAEL: The sermon / Haim Hazaz -- Prophet, Go flee! / Hayyim Nahman Bialik -- They say there is a country / Saul Tchernichovsky -- Afternoon light / Yakov Fichman -- Gleaning / David Shimoni -- Passover in Jerusalem / Avigdor Hameiri -- Put me into the breach / Yehuda Karni -- Israel / Yitzhak Lamdan -- Lord, You Saved me from Ur-Germany as I fled / Uri Tzvi Greenberg -- Drink wonder / S. Shalom -- Negev / David Rokeah -- VI. OTHER EMERGING NATIONS: Saida the Midwife from The Last Faggot / Yaqoub Balboul -- The Little Gods, from Thirsty Hearts / Dhounnoun Ayoub --  In The Night / Chaker Khozbak -- The Wind from the South, from The song of The Earth / Abd el-Malek Nouri -- The Ice-Cream Seller from Puppets and Children / Safira Jamil Hafez -- The Quarrel, from Sisters / Jabra Ibrahim Jabra -- Some New Blood / Mahdi Issa el-Saqr -- The shoeblack / Khogli Choukrallah -- The Past and Us / Maarouf al Rousafi -- Orient and Occident / Chibli Mallat -- Palestine / Salim al Zurkali -- Idealists / Muhammed Hariri -- The question has grown / Wasfi Qronfli -- The Tigris by moonlight / Khalid al Chawaf -- My sister / Jaafar Hamid al Bachir -- Prayer / Boules Salame -- The new Noah / Ali Ahmad Said -- To wash off the shame / Nazik Al Malaika -- Reflections on the occupation / Soleiman al Issa -- Reflections on the occupation / Hilal Naji -- The return / Abdel Wahab al-Bayti -- Sinbad\'s town / Badr Chaker al-Sayeb -- The prisoner / Mubarak Hassan Khalifa -- The girl has awakened / Muhii Al-din Fares -- VII. EXPERIMENTAL LITERATURE: ALIENATION, EXISTENTIALISM, AND THE ABSURD: An uninsured letter. from Until the Last Drop / Fares Zarzour -- The Sacred Well, from the Monster Gods / Layla Balabki -- Autumn / Bichr Fares -- Sunset / Fathi Ghanem -- From The Extinguished Lantern / Fouad Tekerli -- To the men of the twentieth century from the Smoke of My Heart / Al-Taher Wattar -- City of Wrong: A Friday in Jerusalem / M. Kemal Hussein -- The abandoned well / Yousef Al-Khal -- In us, death and beauty / Salma al-Jayoussi -- The age of ice / Khalil Hawi -- Shame / Baland Haidari -- By night / Michel Hayak -- Baghdad in 1954 / Kazim Kawad -- The streets of the town / Jili Abdel Rahman -- Exodus / Saleh Abdel Sabbour -- The drama of Sisyphus / Nourredine Sammoud --  VIII. IRAN, A ROYAL RENAISSANCE -- Conclusion\n\n', '', '', 'Middle Eastern literature from the twentieth century', '', '295 p. ; 27 cm.', '1st ed.', '', '06/14/2006', 'translit', 'book');
