INSERT INTO `main_table` VALUES ('1979', 'Religion', 'Dimashqi', 'Al-Hafiz Ibn Katheer', '', 'al-Ḥāfiẓ ʿIbn Kathīr Dimashqī', 'Dr. Abdul Ahad', 'Faisal Shafiq', 'ʿAbdul Aḥad', 'Fayṣal Shafīq', 'Book of the end', 'Great trials and tribulations', 'Nihāyah fī al-fitan wa al-malāḥim', '', '', 'Darussalam', 'Riyadh', '2006', 'SOME EARLY EVENTS: The prophet intimated that after him Abu Bakr would take charge over the Muslim nation -- The prophet intimated to us that the muslims would conquer Egypt -- The prophet foretold the end of the Persian and Roman empires -- The messenger of Allah prophesized \'Umar\'s murder -- The prophet foretold the trials that \'Uthmaan was to undergo -- The prophet foretold \'Ammaar Ibn Yaasir\'s killing -- The prophet specified that the period of the caliphate was to last for thirty years after his death and then the era of kingdoms would begin -- The prophet gave tidings of Al-Hasan making peace with two huge groups of Muslims -- The messenger of Allah informed Umm Haraam Bint Milhaan that she would die in a naval war -- The prophet indicated that the Muslim army would reach India and Sindh -- The prophet said that the Muslims would fight the Turks -- The prophet intimated that some children would take positions of authority over the Muslims, -- The prophet informed us of twelve Khaleefahs from the Quraish who rule over the Muslim nation -- The Khaleefahs of the Quraish referred to in the Hadeeth -- Narrations mentioning signs related to the year 200 -- The best generation is the generation of the Messenger, then those who came next, then those who came next, -- The Messenger did not specify when this world will come to an end and it is not authentically related -- The narration that speaks about a fire in the land of Hijaaz which will illuminate camels in Busrah, in the land of Sham -- The appearance of a fire in Madeenah that continued -- ABOUT THE HOUR: Narrations from the Prophet that speak about the unseen future -- The Prophet gave news about events from the past and the future -- There is no basis for Israelite narrations that specify how long the world will remain -- The nearness of the hour -- On the day of resurrection, the Muslim will be resurrected with those whom he loves -- Whoever dies, then his hour has arrived -- The keys to the unseen are five: None knows them save Allah -- THE TRIALS, EVENTS, SIGNS: The trials in general -- The Prophet informed us about the rotation of good and evil -- Islam will return strange and new as it had begun -- Division within the nations -- This nation will not gather upon misguidance -- Permission to withdraw from people when trials become severe and when desires become deeply ingrained -- It is forbidden to hope for death -- Knowledge will be raised with the death of the scholars -- The Prophet intimated to us that a group from this nation will remain upon the truth until the Day of Judgment -- A narration which indicates that every 100 years, Allah will send for this nation He (or those) who will revive the affairs of the religion -- Some of the signs of the hour that The Prophet mentioned -- Knowledge will be raised (or taken away) from people at the End of Time -- Evils that will occur at the end of times, of which some are taking place in our age -- The Prophet spoke of evils that were to occur after his time -- The poor will enter paradise before the rich -- The Mahdee -- Who will come at the End of Times; He is one of the rightly-guided Khaleefahs and Imams -- Different trials that have occurred and that will increase in intensity at the End of Times -- If there are many wrongdoers. all will be destroyed, even if there are righteous people among them -- Trials that will occur among Muslims -- Every era that comes is better than the one that follows it -- Trials that Muslims should try to stay away from -- The raising of trustworthiness from the hearts -- The Prophet informed us that the trial will appear from the East -- Trials will increase until the living will envy the dead -- The Prophet informed us that, before the coming of the hour, -- Huge quantity of wealth that will be revealed in Arab lands, and the discord and the death that will result -- The many Dajjals that appear before the hour, and the hour will arrive at a time when people will be heedless of it -- Two categories of people that will inhabit the hellfire, and we seek refuge in Allah, the Lord of all that exists -- Excuses for not ordering others to good and forbidding them from evil -- People will leave the religion in throngs -- Destructive trials -- News from the Messenger of destructive trials that will make the one who adheres to his religion like one who is grasping embers -- New from the Prophet of the nations gathering against the Muslims, seeking to weaken them, even though the Muslims will be large in numbers -- The Messenger intimated that a destructive Fitnah will occur and safety from it achieved by staying far away from it and from ways that lead to it -- Tribulations have a harmful effect on one\'s character, whereby a man will not even be safe from the Companion he sits with -- Different kinds of trials mentioned by the Prophet; the way to escape from them is to withdraw from society -- The messenger of Allah advised that one should bear hardships during tribulations and that one should keep away from participating in evil -- The messenger of Allah informed us that some Muslims will return to idol-worship -- The Fitnah of the saddlebag -- A trial in which the impact of the tongue is more harsh than the impact of the sword -- The Prophet intimated that the Muslims would conquer Constantinople before Rome -- Some news, the source of which is imputed to the Messenger of Allah, about destruction in certain countries; -- Many signs and aayaat -- Signs indicating the proximity of the hour -- The Prophet ordered Muslims to hasten to do good deeds before the occurrence of six matters -- Ten signs before the coming of the hour -- The fire that will come out from the floor (or depth) of \'Adan -- The fierce battle that will take place with the Romans, which will end with the conquering of Constantinople -- ABOUT DAJJAAL: The hour will not arrive until the Maseeh (\'Eesa Ibn Maryam) kills the Dajjaal -- Laailaha Illallah Wallahuakbar (None has the right to be worshipped but allah and Allah is the greatest) -- The conquering of some islands and of the lands of Rome and Persia; -- When the hour arrives, the Romans will be greatest in numbers -- An indication that Al-Madeenah Al-Munawwarah will be faced with weakness when Jerusalem will be inhabited -- Al-Madeenah Al-Munawwarah is protected from plague and from the Dajjaal entering it -- The Prophet pointed out that Al-Madeenah Al-Munawwarah will become developed -- Before the hour there will be liars claiming Prophethood for themselves -- About callers to the hellfire -- MORE AHADEETH ABOUT THE DAJJAAL: Some narrations concerning Ibn Sayyaad -- The Messenger of Allah\'s warning about the Dajjaal, and some of the Dajjaal\'s attributes -- The fire of the Dajjaal is Paradise and his Paradise is fire -- The Messenger warned his nation not to be deceived by what the Dajjaal has with him in terms of apparent strength -- Ibn Sayyaad is not the Greater Dajjaal; and what Tameem Ad-Daaree related in regards to him seeing -- Ibn Sayyaad is from the Jews of Al-Madeenah -- The Hadeeth of An-Nawaas Ibn Sam\'aan Al-Kilaabee -- Sayings ascribed to the Messenger of Allah about strange and wonderful matters -- Various Ahadeeth about the Dajjaal -- Why was not the Dajjaal explicitly mentioned in the noble Qur\'an? -- How to protect oneself from the Dajjaal -- \'EESA IBN MARYAM: The Messenger of Allah \'Eesa Ibn Maryam will descend from the heaven of the earth at the end of time -- Some extraordinary occurrences before the arrival of the hour -- Before the coming of the hour, worship will decrease and wealth will increase -- The prophets are brothers and children of the same father -- The prophet is the most entitled of people to \'Eesa Ibn Maryam -- A description of Al-Maseeh \'Eesa Ibn Maryam, the Messenger of Allah -- Yajooj and Majooj (Gog and Magog) -- The destruction of the Ka\'bah -- The Dajjaal will enter neither Makkah nor Al-Madeenah -- The beast will come out and speak to the people -- Ten signs before the hour -- The sun rising from the west -- The smoke that will occur before the day of resurrection -- There will be much fainting just before the hour (or many people will be struck by lightning) -- Severe rainfall that will occur before the day of Resurrection -- Signs which, if they have not yet occurred, will occur before The Hour -- THE RESURRECTION DAY: The different chains for the Hadeeth: \"I have been sent and the hour like these two\" -- The Hadeeth - When compared to the time that has passed, the Day of Resurrection is indeed near -- Same verses about the Resurrection Day -- The end of this world and the coming of The Hereafter -- The different times that the horn is blown, and nothing remains from a human being except for \'Ajbudh-Dhanab (\"The lowest bone on the spinal cord\") -- The mention of the fire and how it will gather the people to Ash-Sham -- Regarding the Hadeeth of the Horn -- Ahadeeth about The Resurrection -- The day of Resurrection is the day that the trumpet will be blown, for the Resurrection of bodies from their graves, and that will be on a Friday -- The moment when the hour will arrive -- The bodies of the prophets do not decompose in the earth -- On the Day of Resurrection, the first for whom the Earth will split open is the Messenger of Allah -- The mention of the one who will be the first to be dressed at that time -- Man will be raised by the garment of his deeds - whether they are good or bad -- Some of what has been mentioned in the Qur\'an about terrifying events on the Day of Resurrection -- The terrifying, great events that will take place on the Day of Resurrection -- Some of those who will be in the shade of Allah on the Day of Resurrection --  Some of what the haughty ones will be rewarded with on the Day of Resurrection -- The lengthy period of the Day of Resurrection -- Some of the punishments that have been prepared for those who do not pay the Zakaat that is due upon them -- For sinners, The Day of Resurrection is long and difficult; for the people of Taqwaa (Piety, righteousness, etc.) -- The station of praise and glory -- Among the rest of the prophets, is specific to the Messenger of Allah; part of that is the greater intercession for the people of the Mawqif, -- On the day of resurrection, the Messenger will be the chief of the children of Adam -- The Messenger is the Imam of the prophets on the Day of Resurrection -- THE HAUD (BASIN): Narrations related about the Haud (Basin) of Muhammad - May Allah give us drink from it on the Day of Resurrection -- Just some of the eminent companions who believed in the Haud -- Al-Kauthar is a river in Paradise, which the Messenger of Allah was given -- On the Day of Resurrection,  every prophet has a Haud (Basin); they will be vying with one another -- \"Whoever turns away from the Sunnah of The Messenger, the angels will strike his face, (driving him), -- The Messenger feared for his nation that they would compete over this world -- The first to come and drink from The Haud on the Day of Resurrection is he who gave drink to the thirsty one in the world -- \"Whoever drinks from the Haud that people will go to will be prevented from thirst,\" -- Whoever disbelieves in The Haud will not be given drink from it -- Among the prophets, the Messenger will have the most followers on the Day of Resurrection -- Between the grave of the Messenger and his Minbar (Pulpit) is a garden from the gardens of Paradise -- For every prophet there is a Haud (basin) but the Haud of our Prophet is the greatest of them, -- The Auliyaa of Allah )Islamic monotheists who love, fear, and hope from Allah, doing good deeds, -- The Haud that people will come to is before the extended Siraat -- The specifications of the length and width of the Haud differ according to who The Messenger of Allah was addressing; he mentioned for each person places that he knew -- Allah will come on the Day of Resurrection to rule between his slaves -- The speech of the Lord with the messengers on the Day of Resurrection -- Allah\'s speech with Adam on the Day of Resurrection -- Allah\'s speech with Noah and Allah\'s questioning of him regarding whether he conveyed -- Bestowal of honor upon Ibraaheem before all who are present on the Day of Resurrection -- \'Eesa and Allah\'s speech with him on the Day of Resurrection -- The station of the Messenger of Allah with Allah on the Day of Resurrection - No other station comes near to it in status -- Allah\'s speech with the scholars during the passing of judgment -- The first saying of Allah to the believers -- No share in the hereafter will he have who betrays the trust and covenant of Allah -- The presentation of the fires and the gardens, and the erection of the Meezaan (Scale), and the accountability with Allah -- At the place of gathering, an eye from the hellfire will be shown, and it will look over the people -- THE MENTION OF THE BALANCE (SCALE): A neck from the fire will come out and speak; the haughty ones, the Mushrikeen -- The mention of the balance (Scale) -- The weighing of deeds after the judgment and the reckoning -- The balance has two scales that have a physical reality; and Bismillahir-Rahmaanir-Raheem -- On the Day of Resurrection, the testimony of \"None has the right to be worshipped but Allah\" -- A good character is the heaviest thing that will be placed in the balance of the slave on the Day of Resurrection -- The sayings of the scholars regarding the Tafseer of the balance that will exist on the Day of Resurrection -- On the Day of Resurrection, the balance is not for every single individual -- TAKING OF ACCOUNT:  When deeds will be presented before Allah, when the scrolls will be scattered, and when the Lord calls his slaves to the accountability -- Whoever\' s taking of account is discussed, is destroyed -- The first matter that will be judged upon on the Day of Resurrection will be blood (i.e. The shedding of blood) -- The first nation to have their account taken on the Day of Resurrection is the Nation of Muhammad -- The mention of the first matter that Allah will rule upon between people on the Day of Resurrection; -- Whoever wrongs another by wrongfully taking a piece of land will be enveloped by it from seven earths on the Day of Resurrection -- The punishment of the picture-takers and the ones who make three-dimensional statues on the Day of Resurrection -- On the Day of Resurrection, the two feet of the slave will remain on the Land of the Mahshar -- On the Day of Resurrection, the first matter that one will be held accountable for is the prayer -- Retribution exacted from the wrongdoers on the Day of Resurrection -- Ash-Shirk Billah (Associating partners with Allah) is not forgiven, and wrong done among the slaves -- Dying in the way of Allah expiates all things except for the trust -- On the Day of Resurrection, the slave will be asked about the delights (He indulged in, this world) -- It is mentioned that Allah will make certain of his slaves to be reconciled to one another -- A mention of those who will enter Paradise from this nation without any reckoning (i.e., without facing the taking of accounts) -- How the people will be separated from the place where they were gathered for accountability; then one group is for Paradise and one group is for The Hellfire -- The last of the people of the Paradise to enter it -- A MENTION OF THE SIRAAT (PATH OVER THE HELLFIRE): From other than what has been mentioned in the previously mentioned Ahadeeth -- Some attributes of the people of Paradise and some of the delights that have been prepared for them -- Some of what has been relegated regarding the age of the inhabitants of Paradise -- The severe torment inside of it: May Allah protect us from it by his mercy; indeed he is most munificent, most generous -- A mention of the hellfire and its extreme blackness - May allah protect us from it -- The hellfire - and we seek refuge in Allah - is 70 times more fierce than the fire of this world -- The hellfire was ignited for 3000 years until it became black and dark -- The heat of the hellfire never goes out and one does not warm oneself by its flame -- The hellfire complained to its Lord that it was eating itself -- The severe heat of hell is hotter than all else -- When the richest and most comfortable of people in the world from the dwellers of the Hellfire is dipped into it -- If a disbeliever had enough gold to fill the Earth and then tried to ransom himself from the punishment on the Day of Resurrection -- On the Day of Resurrection, the believer will hope to return to the world in order to fight in the way of Allah -- A description of the Hellfire and the hugeness of its inhabitants -- The depth of hell is the distance it takes for a thrown rock to fall for seventy years -- The hugeness of their bodies in the Hellfire - May Allah protect us from their situation -- The ugliness of the disbeliever and the hugeness of his body in the fire of hell on the day of resurrection -- A mention of the sea burning in hell and being a part of hell -- The gates of hell and a description of its keepers and its guards - May Allah protect us from it -- A description of the Siraat (Path over hell) and the disparity of speed with which the people cross over it -- The food and drink of the people of hell -- Those Ahadeeth which mention its names: Which of them are authentic and which of them are otherwise? -- A prison in hell that is called Boolus - May Allah Azza wa-Jall (To him belongs might and majesty) protect us from it -- The well of grief -- A river in hell which is like the filth, waste, and putrid material in the world - we ask Allah to protect us from it by his grace and favor -- The valley of Lamlam -- A valley with a well in Hell, the valley is called Habhab -- The mention of wail and Sa\'ood -- Its snakes and its lizards - May Allah protect us from it and from them -- A sermon containing an admonition, which should encourage and at the same time instill fear in one who has a heart or one who listens attentively -- The mercy of Allah is near to him who sincerely seeks refuge with Allah from the heat of the Hellfire and from its bitter cold -- The lowest levels of hell - We seek refuge in Allah from its punishment -- Some of the snakes in Hell -- And we seek refuge in Allah -- The crying of the people of the hellfire when they are in the hellfire - We ask Allah Azza wa-Jall -- Various Ahadeeth pertaining to the description of Hell and its inhabitants -- THE INTERCESSION OF THE MESSENGER OF ALLAH: The greater intercession -- What honors and tasks the Messenger of Allah is singled out with from among all of the prophets -- Another kind of intercession is one for whom intercession is made so that he enters Paradise without any accountability -- Knowledge of the intercession was lost to the Khawarij and the Mo\'tazilah, and so they denied it -- The chains and wordings of Ahadeeth related about the intercession of the believers for their families -- The people of Al-Araaf -- A mention of the first one to come out of the hellfire and then enter Paradise -- THE RIVERS OF PARADISE, ITS TREES, AND ITS FRUITS: A description of the people of Paradise and of the bliss that is found in Paradise -- The names of the gates of Paradise -- The key to Paradise is the testimony of \"None has the right to be worshipped but Allah -- The mention of different places in paradise as well as of their elevation and vastness -- Few deeds in the way of allah are better than the world and that which is in it -- Al-Firdaus is the highest level in Paradise -- prayer and fasting necessitate the forgiveness of Allah \'Azza wa Jall -- The levels of Paradise differ, and none knows the degree of those differences except for Allah -- A mention of what the dweller of Paradise with the lowest ranking will receive -- A mention of the rooms of Paradise, their elevation, vastness, and hugeness -- The abodes in Paradise of those who love one another for Allah -- A mention of the highest station in Paradise; it is the Al-Waseelah therein - The station of the Messenger of Allah -- The structures of the castles of Paradise: What are they made of? -- The mention of pavilions in Paradise -- Mention of the soil in Paradise -- The rivers of Paradise, its trees, and its fruits -- A description of Al-Kauthar, the most famous of the rivers of Paradise. May Allah give us drink from it, by his grace and generosity -- A mention of the Al-Baidakh river in Paradise -- A shining river at the gate of Paradise -- The trees of Paradise -- The fruits of Paradise, we ask Allah to make us taste from them, by his grace and generosity - Ameen -- The food and drink of the inhabitants of Paradise; we ask Allah by his grace to bestow all of that upon us -- Some of the people of Paradise will want to farm. Then Allah will answer them their wish -- A mention of the first food that the inhabitants of Paradise will eat -- The clothing of the dwellers of Paradise; their adornments, garments and beauty - We ask Allah from all of that -- A description of the couches for the dwellers of Paradise -- Adornment of Al-Hoor (Beautiful women in Paradise) Al-Een (Who have beautiful, wide eyes) -- Sexual intercourse of the people of Paradise with their women, and they shall not have children except if one of them desires so -- What has been said about the granting of children to the people of Paradise -- THE DWELLERS OF PARADISE: Their lives are complete and perfect, for they do not die, and they continue to increase in the strength of their youth, the freshness of their faces, the beauty of their forms, -- The good pleasure of Allah: that is over and above what they have with them -- A mention of the Lord looking at them and a mention of them looking at him - How perfect he is! -- A mention of the dwellers of Paradise looking at their Lord \'Azza wa Jall -- The ground of Paradise as well as the goodness and spreading of its good fragrance -- The light and splendor of Paradise, and its beautiful scenery in the morning and in the evening -- Allah encouraged his slaves to seek out Paradise and to hasten towards it -- Whoever seeks protection with Allah from Hellfire, then He will protect him, -- Paradise and the Hellfire seek out and are granted intercession -- Paradise is surrounded by Difficulties, i.e. difficult deeds, in terms of performing good deeds while abstaining -- The dwellers of Paradise will visit one another; they will gather and reminisce about their affairs in the world, A comprehensive chapter regarding rulings pertaining to Paradise and to various Ahadeeth -- The grace and generosity of Allah \'Azza wa-Jall (To him belongs Might and Majesty) -- Paradise and the Hellfire exist -- Some attributes of the people of Paradise and some attributes of the people of the Hellfire -- The poor ones from this nation will enter Paradise 500 years before the rich ones from it -- The first three to enter Paradise and the first three to enter the Hellfire -- The people of the nation of Muhammad constitute the greatest number of dwellers in Paradise and they are the highest in ranking and degree -- The people of the first generation, the companions of the Messenger of Allah, are the best of this nation -- Some narrations which mention that a large number of people from this nation will enter Paradise without reckoning -- Paradise and the Hellfire exist now, they have already been created, a view that is contrary to what the people of falsehood purport -- A woman might have been married to more than one man during her lifetime; in Paradise,                                ', '', '', 'Includes bibliographical references.', '', '748 p. ; 24 cm.', '', '9960971589', '04/12/2007', 'translit', 'book');
